---
import burnerV from "../../assets/images/Burners/burnerVideo.mp4";
---
<section class="w-full mt-20 md:mt-32 font-bold text-grisT flex flex-col gap-6 px-8 md:px-32">
    <div class="w-full">
        <h1 class="text-3xl md:text-4xl">BURNERS</h1><br>
        <p class="text-base md:text-lg">Triaso® 'Total Air' Burners are designed for complete and efficient fuel combustion, using a fully sealed system that doesn’t
             rely on the drum’s exhaust. This avoids pollution, mix contamination, and filter clogging—while saving fuel and maintaining
              consistent performance throughout the day. Their precise air control system ensures clean operation, low emissions, and reliable 
              results in any climate.
        </p>
    </div>
    <div class="w-1/2 flex justify-center mx-auto">
        <video src={burnerV} autoplay class="w-full"></video>
    </div>
    <div class="text-center">
        <h2 class="text-black text-xl md:text-2xl">
            From 6 to 125 million Btu/Hr, with preheater and filter
        </h2>
    </div>
    <div class="w-full grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 gap-10">
        <div class="w-full text-blueMain flex flex-col gap-3">
            <h2 class="text-lg md:text-xl text-center">Low Nox emissions</h2>
            <div class="w-full h-[2px] bg-blueMain"></div>
            <p class="text-base md:text-lg text-justify">
                Low NOx emissions <span class="text-grisPPP">(nitrogen oxides), a greenhouse gas that is highly regulated in some regions. It 
                can be equipped with a flame protection system to completely reduce NOx to zero. <br>
                 By achieving total combustion, several types of problems are avoided:</span>
            </p>
            <ul class="text-base md:text-lg list-disc ml-6"> 
                <li>Atmospheric pollution.</li>
                <li>Contamination of the asphalt mix with unburned fuel.</li>
                <li>Clogging in the baghouse and a high risk of fire.</li>
            </ul>
        </div>
        <div class="w-full text-redBg flex flex-col gap-3">
            <h2 class="text-lg md:text-xl text-center">100% regulated air</h2>
            <div class="w-full h-[2px] bg-redBg"></div>
            <p class="text-base md:text-lg text-justify text-grisPPP">
                The burner regulates <span class="text-redBg"> 100% of the air for combustion </span>without help from the drum's exhaust 
                system. This achieves total combustion, <span class="text-redBg">ensuring 100% fuel utilization</span>.
            </p>
            <ul class="text-base md:text-lg list-disc ml-6 text-grisPPP"> 
                <li>Sealed installation, without cold air inlets, saving the fuel used to heat it, allowing for precise and efficient carburation.</li>
                <li>Efficiency is not affected by changes in weather temperature throughout the day.</li>
            </ul>
        </div>
    </div>
</section>